00:43:07.460 --> 00:43:11.159
So my question is, do you have any advice

00:43:11.159 --> 00:43:13.679
for maintaining stakeholder engagement

00:43:13.679 --> 00:43:16.919
for in-house data science requests or projects

00:43:16.919 --> 00:43:21.799
before they turn to an external vendor product?

00:43:21.799 --> 00:43:23.080
You know, in a fast-paced world,

00:43:23.080 --> 00:43:24.440
which there's lots of pressure

00:43:24.440 --> 00:43:28.159
to show excellent results quickly,

00:43:28.159 --> 00:43:29.739
this can be challenging.

00:43:30.619 --> 00:43:35.479
Yeah, that's double-edged sword, actually,

00:43:35.479 --> 00:43:40.479
because depending on the speed they wanna move at

00:43:41.320 --> 00:43:44.320
and the stakes of the decision,

00:43:44.320 --> 00:43:46.440
you know, you could intercept the train,

00:43:46.919 --> 00:43:49.619
but you might not like the consequences of doing so.

00:43:50.799 --> 00:43:53.119
You know, when they're making decisions

00:43:53.119 --> 00:43:55.080
potentially to evaluate, you know,

00:43:55.080 --> 00:43:58.280
putting you on a project or going with an external vendor

00:43:58.280 --> 00:44:00.280
or third-party solution, you know,

00:44:00.280 --> 00:44:02.239
have that conversation and find out

00:44:02.239 --> 00:44:04.039
what goes into this decision matrix,

00:44:04.039 --> 00:44:06.919
how are you evaluating how to make this decision?

00:44:06.919 --> 00:44:08.039
You know, and then be honest.

00:44:08.039 --> 00:44:09.880
You know, if I were to take it on,

00:44:09.880 --> 00:44:11.679
this is what I can bring to the table

00:44:11.679 --> 00:44:14.520
that going externally won't be able to accomplish,

00:44:14.559 --> 00:44:17.479
and this is why you should go with me instead,

00:44:17.479 --> 00:44:19.080
and also be honest with the trade-offs.

00:44:19.080 --> 00:44:22.520
But by the way, you know, I haven't, you know,

00:44:22.520 --> 00:44:24.400
I don't have experience in this particular domain

00:44:24.400 --> 00:44:25.880
or I haven't done this specific layer.

00:44:25.880 --> 00:44:27.080
It will take me a bit longer.

00:44:27.080 --> 00:44:29.080
And then, you know, be really honest,

00:44:29.080 --> 00:44:31.580
which is if you were the business stakeholder

00:44:31.580 --> 00:44:33.520
and you just heard the argument you made

00:44:33.520 --> 00:44:35.479
for why they should go with you,

00:44:35.479 --> 00:44:37.599
would you choose to go with you,

00:44:37.599 --> 00:44:39.200
or is there enough risk here

00:44:39.200 --> 00:44:42.260
that they really do need to go with an external solution?

00:44:42.260 --> 00:44:43.099
And, you know, obviously,

00:44:43.099 --> 00:44:45.219
the context and the details really matter,

00:44:45.219 --> 00:44:49.539
but put yourself in the mindset of the business stakeholder

00:44:49.539 --> 00:44:52.780
and understand how are they going to make this decision,

00:44:52.780 --> 00:44:55.799
and is it really in their best interest

00:44:55.799 --> 00:44:57.900
to keep it internal versus going external?

00:44:59.859 --> 00:45:01.299
Great points.

00:45:01.299 --> 00:45:03.780
Also, maybe think about the opportunity costs

00:45:03.780 --> 00:45:07.020
of them choosing you for maintaining it in-house,

00:45:07.020 --> 00:45:08.239
because if there's other things

00:45:08.239 --> 00:45:09.940
that the data science team could be doing

00:45:09.940 --> 00:45:11.679
that are much more valuable than that thing

00:45:11.679 --> 00:45:14.239
that they're potentially gonna vendor out,

00:45:15.520 --> 00:45:17.179
it might be a hard sell for them.

00:45:18.760 --> 00:45:19.900
My two cents.

